│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ I will modify the constructor body to call `setDisableInstructionReassociation(true)` on both expander instances. This will prevent them from reusing any existing instructions from the │
│ function, forcing them to generate new, private instructions for the runtime checks. This ensures that the generated code is completely isolated and can be safely deleted by the        │
│ cleaner.                                                                                                                                                                                 │
